# ğŸ§® Find Pivot Index

## ğŸ“ Problem Statement
Given an array of integers nums, calculate the pivot index of this array.The pivot index is the index where the sum of all the numbers strictly to the left of the index is equal to the sum of all the numbers strictly to the index's right.
If the index is on the left edge of the array, then the left sum is 0 because there are no elements to the left. This also applies to the right edge of the array.
Return the leftmost pivot index. If no such index exists, return -1.
---
## ğŸ“Œ Example
**Input:**  
nums = [1,7,3,6,5,6]
**Output:** 
3
**Explanation:** 
The pivot index is 3.
Left sum = nums[0] + nums[1] + nums[2] = 1 + 7 + 3 = 11
Right sum = nums[4] + nums[5] = 5 + 6 = 11
---

## ğŸ’¡ Approach
1. Compute the total sum of all elements in the array.

2. Initialize leftSum = 0.

3. Traverse the array:

   For index i, calculate
   rightSum = total - leftSum - nums[i]

   If leftSum == rightSum, return i (pivot found).

   Otherwise, add nums[i] to leftSum and move on.
4. If no pivot index satisfies the condition, return -1.
---
## â± Time Complexity
O(N) - One pass to compute total, one pass to find pivot

## ğŸ’¾ Space Complexity
O(1)

---

## ğŸ§‘â€ğŸ’» Java Code

```java
class Solution {
    public int pivotIndex(int[] nums) {
        int leftSum = 0;
        int total = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
            total += nums[i];
        }
        for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
            int rightSum = total - leftSum - nums[i];
            if (rightSum == leftSum) {
                return i;
            }
            leftSum += nums[i];
        }
        return -1;
    }
}
